author: Nicole Saavedra
title: Jefferson, Prince Avenue Christian hold on to spots in high school football polls
text:
Jefferson, Prince Avenue Christian hold on to spots in high school football polls Jefferson and Prince Avenue Christian hung on to their spots in their respective high school football polls, which were released by the Georgia Sports Writers Association Tuesday. 
Jefferson (8-0, 4-0 in Region 8-AAA) is ranked third in Class AAA after posting its second consecutive shutout in a 49-0 win over East Jackson Friday. The Dragons are off this week before traveling to Oconee County on Oct. 30. Oconee County (6-1, 3-0) is receiving votes in the poll, and will visit Hart County at 7:30 p.m. Friday. 
Prince Avenue (8-0, 6-0 in Region 8-A) is ranked second in Class A following its 42-14 win over Towns County. The Wolverines will have a week off before hosting Lakeview Academy on Oct. 30. Athens Academy (6-1, 4-1) is also receiving votes. The Spartans will visit Providence Christian Friday.
